The paper focuses on developing optimization approaches for distance metrics in clustering and classification, which are core topics in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies the proposed method to image and medical datasets, indicating a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. The paper mentions the ability to enable active learning, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the computational performance of the algorithms, which could be relevant to scientific computing (cs.SI).
